What is redis?
Redis - Remote Dictinary Server
it is an open source, in memory database(Keeps all data in RAM → blazing fast read/write speeds.)
primarily used for database, cache
It stores key-value pairs — think of it like a super-fast, temporary database.
Can persist data to disk if needed, but speed comes from RAM.
Supports advanced data structures: strings, hashes, lists, sets, sorted sets, bitmaps, streams, etc.
 It supports pub/sub, which enables real time communication b/w clients and also helps in transactions


 use cases
 - caching
 - session management
 - Real time analytics